  "text": "Gibbsite: Al(OH) [CITATION_1] In Differential Thermal Analysis (DTA) these decompositions are observed as endothermic peaks in the DTA thermal curves. Since these decompositions are associated with the evolution of water vapor, they are also observed as weight loss events in Thermogravimetry (TGA) and Derivative Thermogravimetry (DTG) . It should be mentioned that the loss of a certain amount of adsorbed water is also observed by both TGA/DTG and DTA methods of analysis. This will be shown in the corresponding TGA/DTG thermal curves obtained Advances in Applied Chemistry and Biochemistry ISSN: 2652-3175 . 02 .",
